        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Luajit can't calculate the version since we're currently downloading the tarball which doesn't have the `.git` directory. I see the following options we can take:\r\n\r\n1. accept the PR as is.\r\n2. Use `GIT_REPOSITORY` instead of `URL` to specify the git repo as the dependency rather than the tarball. A disadvantage is that we won't be able to use SHA256 to verify if we got the expected code. Another is that if we go this route then the executable name will change with every version change, but this is a minor annoyance that should be easily fixable.\r\n\r\nI'd lean for option 1 currently unless we find more advantages of option 2. An advantage might be that we can start specifying the minimum luajit version, assuming the version numbers are monotonically increasing and not random nonsense.",
