        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The last number in the semver is a monotonic *timestamp*, not a hash.\r\n\r\nBy trusting a git hash you're automatically creating a trust chain down to the individual files. That is, if you trust your git client. Right now, you're trusting the hash of a derivative made by a third party.\r\n\r\nThe missing symlink was an oversight and is now fixed, thanks to the report by @clason.\r\n\r\n`DESTDIR` must be an absolute path, use `$PWD` and not a dot. See https://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/html_node/DESTDIR.html.\r\n\r\nAnd, yes, please cache all repos centrally in your build system to avoid hundreds of build processes permanently pulling the git repo.",
